WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:16.140 --> 00:00:18.014
﻿Plasma Youth Sports Games
with Unsuccess of the champion,

00:00:18.068 --> 00:00:20.201
would like to thank Slaven Bilić
for stepping in as the host.

00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:23.279
Bilić is one of the first sponsors,
ambassador and is our biggest promoter.

00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:25.913
He used his life and sports experience
in order to prepare high-quality content

00:00:25.997 --> 00:00:27.957
with his guests for all generations.
Thanks, Nane!

00:00:30.540 --> 00:00:32.780
Have you ever thought
about giving up?

00:00:32.980 --> 00:00:37.620
Have you ever cried? Are you emotional?
Personally, I think you are.

00:00:38.380 --> 00:00:42.814
It is hard to achieve all of this alone.
-Everyone thinks that I am...

00:00:42.921 --> 00:00:45.712
When people see Ibra, they think
he is strong, big, a man of steel.

00:00:45.895 --> 00:00:49.251
However, if you got to know me better,
you would say that I have a big heart.

00:00:49.404 --> 00:00:52.337
That's not just my opinion.
I am very sensitive.

00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:56.740
Those who find themselves inside
my world know this. -Yes.

00:00:57.100 --> 00:00:59.580
I am ready to do everything
to protect you.

00:01:00.860 --> 00:01:06.580
Words mean much more to me
than anything else. That's just how I am.

00:01:06.780 --> 00:01:10.185
However, it takes a lot of time
for me to accept someone.

00:01:10.363 --> 00:01:13.185
In the past, some bad situations
happened to me,

00:01:13.346 --> 00:01:16.833
and that's why I find it very hard
to let people be part of my world.

00:01:16.937 --> 00:01:20.365
Many people asked things of me
and I... -You put up a barrier.

00:01:20.473 --> 00:01:23.661
Today that barrier exists,
and it didn't before.

00:01:25.180 --> 00:01:29.500
For all those mistakes I made,
I paid the price...

00:01:29.700 --> 00:01:33.100
Otherwise, I am a very sensitive.

00:01:34.020 --> 00:01:36.407
People only notice that
when I accept them as friends.

00:01:36.513 --> 00:01:38.461
But toward everyone else,
I behave differently.

00:01:38.547 --> 00:01:40.523
And you know very well
what the football world is like,

00:01:40.634 --> 00:01:42.923
because you were a player,
and today you are a coach.

00:01:43.229 --> 00:01:46.810
Football is a dirty world.
-That's right.

00:01:46.933 --> 00:01:50.052
I don't know how to describe it better.
-Yes, it's a dirty world.

00:01:50.740 --> 00:01:53.620
It is an aggressive and dirty world.

00:01:53.940 --> 00:01:56.740
Because it is the biggest sport
in the world, and because

00:01:56.920 --> 00:01:59.380
enormous amounts of money
circulate within it.

00:01:59.620 --> 00:02:03.300
Everyone has their own interests
that they want to achieve.

00:02:03.980 --> 00:02:06.300
So everything is for sale.

00:02:06.940 --> 00:02:09.740
I was one of those players
who agreed to transfers.

00:02:09.980 --> 00:02:15.500
I signed contracts, I played in Spain,
France, England, Italy, and in the USA.

00:02:15.700 --> 00:02:20.140
In the USA, I spent less time as a player
because the situation is different there.

00:02:20.380 --> 00:02:25.513
My late agent was wow.
I've seen everything.

00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:32.591
I know how things work.
"You eat, or you get eaten."

00:02:33.687 --> 00:02:36.052
That world is like that.

00:02:36.180 --> 00:02:38.940
That's why I said earlier,
when you asked me...

00:02:39.180 --> 00:02:42.820
I didn't have anyone to help me.
I only had my self-confidence.

00:02:43.020 --> 00:02:47.220
Some people told me
that it's important to be arrogant,

00:02:47.420 --> 00:02:49.380
but I had self-confidence.

00:02:51.220 --> 00:02:56.660
I learned to believe in myself.
-Yes, believe in yourself.

00:02:56.900 --> 00:03:00.820
I believed in myself so strongly
that no one could stop me.

00:03:00.980 --> 00:03:07.860
Or block me. That's why I never
thought about quitting football.

00:03:08.300 --> 00:03:10.220
That's why, for such a long time...

00:03:10.500 --> 00:03:19.940
The more people didn't believe in me,
the more motivation I had.

00:03:20.180 --> 00:03:25.522
It's about motivation.
-But that happened to me suddenly.

00:03:26.506 --> 00:03:35.469
They did not immediately
predict a bright career for me.

00:03:36.298 --> 00:03:39.193
His fate is already written.

00:03:39.530 --> 00:03:44.490
It wasn't obvious at first.
I had that self-confidence.

00:03:45.980 --> 00:03:49.260
I set myself the goal that I want
to be the best player in the world.

00:03:49.660 --> 00:03:53.260
In high school, one of my
subjects was the Italian language.

00:03:53.460 --> 00:03:59.420
One day the teacher told me...
because I was not a good student.

00:03:59.620 --> 00:04:04.447
In class I was always talking
and didn't behave properly.

00:04:04.681 --> 00:04:07.521
I disturbed other students.
-You were mischievous.

00:04:07.745 --> 00:04:10.745
And then one day the teacher said to me:
"You will never amount to anything."

00:04:10.913 --> 00:04:13.603
That happened in Italian class.

00:04:13.816 --> 00:04:17.564
I told her the following: "I will be
a professional footballer in Italy.

00:04:17.728 --> 00:04:21.288
And I will learn Italian so well
that I will come back here

00:04:21.530 --> 00:04:26.626
to Sweden and teach you."
-Really? -I did.

00:04:26.877 --> 00:04:30.845
After that, I never went
back to that school again.

00:04:31.860 --> 00:04:36.548
I was thinking only about the fact
that I didn't want anyone

00:04:37.679 --> 00:04:43.884
to hold me back. I was ready to give
200% to succeed. -To prove it.

00:04:44.580 --> 00:04:53.919
When I was 17, in Malmö a player
came on trial from Trinidad and Tobago.

00:04:54.637 --> 00:04:56.788
He started training with us.

00:04:57.022 --> 00:05:01.810
At that time, I was playing for both
the first and the second team.

00:05:02.653 --> 00:05:06.083
In one of the matches
I played for the second team...

00:05:06.402 --> 00:05:11.202
After seven days of his arrival,
he said this to me:

00:05:11.599 --> 00:05:15.119
"If you don't succeed,
it's your own fault."

00:05:15.500 --> 00:05:17.900
I started thinking about that.

00:05:18.140 --> 00:05:22.980
He also told me that
if I didn't want to succeed,

00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:25.700
it would be only my fault.

00:05:25.900 --> 00:05:30.060
At that time, I was only 17 years old
and I wondered why he told me that.

00:05:30.260 --> 00:05:38.060
I didn't ask for his opinion or what
he wanted to achieve by saying it.

00:05:38.780 --> 00:05:42.380
While I was walking home,
I kept thinking about why he said it.

00:05:42.620 --> 00:05:44.460
He doesn't even know who I am.

00:05:44.660 --> 00:05:48.940
He has no interest in me,
he just came on trial.

00:05:49.940 --> 00:05:55.070
I thought there were only two things,
either he wanted to play in my position,

00:05:55.187 --> 00:05:57.437
he simply wanted to help me.

00:05:57.626 --> 00:06:01.490
Or he was giving me a signal
for something else.

00:06:01.946 --> 00:06:06.920
In the end, I realized that everything
in life depends only on me.

00:06:07.797 --> 00:06:11.857
If I fail to become the best player,
it will be only my fault. Not others.

00:06:12.032 --> 00:06:14.592
But that's also a big responsibility.

00:06:14.780 --> 00:06:19.460
Suddenly, I understood
that he was giving me a signal.

00:06:19.940 --> 00:06:24.220
This is good, but that's a lot of
pressure, as a kid.

00:06:24.780 --> 00:06:27.700
It's easy for you to talk about that
now when you're 44 years old.

00:06:27.980 --> 00:06:32.300
But when you're 17,
that's a lot. -You're right.

00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:38.460
The good thing is that you got
a chance in Malmö.

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:42.980
It's a big club...
-It's the best thing that happened.

00:06:43.220 --> 00:06:47.180
You got the chance to play,
fame and you go to Ajax. -Yes.

00:06:47.420 --> 00:06:49.300
You were very young at the time.
-I was young.

00:06:49.580 --> 00:06:54.140
At the age of 20, you move to Ajax,
where Koeman was the coach.

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:58.180
No, Co Adriaanse. He was the first.
-You're right.

00:06:58.460 --> 00:07:02.660
Later, Koeman became your coach.
-Van Gaal was the director.

00:07:02.900 --> 00:07:06.980
Van Basten also helped out,
-That's right. -Was that a big step up?

00:07:07.180 --> 00:07:10.340
Ajax is an outstanding club
for development,

00:07:10.540 --> 00:07:17.060
but were you actually ready for it?
-No, I wasn't.

00:07:17.940 --> 00:07:22.140
What I had in Malmö
was my environment, my home.

00:07:22.380 --> 00:07:25.220
I knew how to deal with
whatever came up.

00:07:25.460 --> 00:07:28.258
If a problem arose,
I knew exactly where to solve it,

00:07:28.442 --> 00:07:30.858
and if not there,
I knew where to go next.

00:07:31.081 --> 00:07:34.711
Everything was within five minutes,
my mother, my father, and the life I knew.

00:07:34.893 --> 00:07:38.867
You were in your comfort zone.
-Yes. I lived alone for six months.

00:07:39.081 --> 00:07:41.761
You could say I lived within
a kind of triangle.

00:07:41.930 --> 00:07:46.650
In Malmö, I had people around me,
friends, I knew the city, every street…

00:07:46.781 --> 00:07:51.021
You had your own structure.
-Exactly. Then I moved to a new club

00:07:51.166 --> 00:07:53.846
that bought me for a record fee.

00:07:55.700 --> 00:08:00.220
The pressure was enormous right
from the start. -Through the roof.

00:08:00.500 --> 00:08:06.780
Stress, pressure, expectations,
results... It was a new world for me.

00:08:06.980 --> 00:08:11.460
I wasn't given enough time,
there was no patience. -Patience...

00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:14.380
They wanted results immediately.

00:08:14.580 --> 00:08:19.700
When I arrived there, I didn't have
any money for the first month

00:08:19.900 --> 00:08:22.220
because salaries were paid
at the end of the month.

00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:29.460
I had a house, I bought a television,
a couch, and a bed and that was it.

00:08:30.140 --> 00:08:38.100
I stayed in Malmö for another six
months after Ajax had bought me,

00:08:38.340 --> 00:08:44.658
because the Swedish season runs
differently from the rest of Europe.

00:08:45.220 --> 00:08:49.620
I had those six months to prepare,
but I lacked experience.

00:08:49.820 --> 00:08:53.460
I bought a bed and a bigger television
than the one I had before

00:08:53.740 --> 00:09:00.380
because I like watching on a big screen.
That couch and that TV...

00:09:00.580 --> 00:09:04.100
When I arrived there,
the fridge was empty,

00:09:04.269 --> 00:09:06.515
and I didn't have money to buy food.

00:09:06.666 --> 00:09:12.437
I spoke to Maxwell, the Brazilian player,
and told him I had nothing left.

00:09:12.578 --> 00:09:16.125
I went to the club and asked if I could
get my salary earlier... -An advance?

00:09:16.320 --> 00:09:20.480
...ahead of time,
so I could live normally.

00:09:21.780 --> 00:09:24.556
They told me it wasn't possible,
that it didn't work that way,

00:09:24.731 --> 00:09:26.931
and that salaries were paid
at the end of the month.

00:09:27.060 --> 00:09:29.820
I went back to Maxwell
and told him I had to live with him

00:09:30.091 --> 00:09:34.181
because I had nothing. He had already
sorted himself out, he arrived prepared,

00:09:34.333 --> 00:09:40.173
he was more mature than I was.
I slept on an IKEA mattress

00:09:40.564 --> 00:09:43.484
on the floor at his place.
I stayed with him for three weeks,

00:09:43.613 --> 00:09:45.978
sleeping there, eating there,
and going to training together.

00:09:46.123 --> 00:09:49.181
And he had arrived at the club
at the same time as I did.

00:09:51.085 --> 00:09:53.325
That's how it all began.

00:09:53.680 --> 00:09:56.900
We went to a tournament in Amsterdam.

00:09:57.540 --> 00:10:04.300
Ajax, Milan, Arsenal and a few
other clubs were taking part.

00:10:04.540 --> 00:10:08.460
During the match against Milan,
I was overflowing with adrenaline.

00:10:08.660 --> 00:10:13.788
I was playing for Ajax, in front of
45,000 people, against Milan players

00:10:13.923 --> 00:10:16.827
I had previously only played
with on the PlayStation.

00:10:16.924 --> 00:10:19.788
I wasn't in Malmö anymore.
I was full of adrenaline,

00:10:19.903 --> 00:10:22.863
but I arrived with confidence.

00:10:23.332 --> 00:10:27.765
It wasn't that I lacked respect
for others, but I genuinely felt

00:10:28.124 --> 00:10:31.609
I was better than them.
That was my mindset.

00:10:31.874 --> 00:10:37.114
I played that match,
the crowd went crazy,

00:10:37.357 --> 00:10:39.929
they couldn't believe
what they were seeing.

00:10:40.077 --> 00:10:42.881
They weren't used to watching
a player who was 1.90 meters tall

00:10:43.012 --> 00:10:45.296
playing football that way.

00:10:49.135 --> 00:10:54.054
In the match against Arsenal,
I was making moves,

00:10:54.418 --> 00:10:58.937
or actually, I think it was Manchester Utd,
when Laurent Blanc was there,

00:10:59.660 --> 00:11:02.580
I made another significant move
and scored a goal.

00:11:02.780 --> 00:11:06.700
Everything looked perfect. Everyone
was saying I was the new Van Basten.

00:11:06.830 --> 00:11:09.150
And then everything
started to go downhill.

00:11:09.274 --> 00:11:15.132
People expected me, like Van Basten,
to score in every single match.

00:11:15.294 --> 00:11:17.357
That you would always play like that...

00:11:17.750 --> 00:11:22.820
However, what I learned back
then applies to all players.

00:11:23.036 --> 00:11:27.257
When you arrive at a new club,
your adrenaline level is exceptionally high.

00:11:27.468 --> 00:11:30.348
You only truly understand
what kind of player you are

00:11:30.502 --> 00:11:33.194
once that adrenaline wears off.
-When you return to a normal level...

00:11:33.471 --> 00:11:38.265
Only then do you really see where
you stand, what you are missing,

00:11:38.566 --> 00:11:42.246
and what you need to work on. At
the beginning everything feels incredible,

00:11:42.446 --> 00:11:47.039
and adrenaline pushes you as if you're
moving at 200 kilometers per hour.

00:11:47.692 --> 00:11:52.140
When the adrenaline fades,
that's when you start to understand

00:11:52.308 --> 00:11:55.632
where you truly are and
what the real situation is.

00:11:56.174 --> 00:12:01.414
When my adrenaline dropped, I was
no longer playing as well as before.

00:12:01.770 --> 00:12:05.085
The coach, Co Adriaanse,
didn't want to talk to me.

00:12:05.203 --> 00:12:08.683
That's strange. -Leo Beenhakker
was there as well, and he was good...

00:12:08.813 --> 00:12:11.093
He was at Real Madrid, right?
-Yes, he was excellent.

00:12:11.239 --> 00:12:17.437
He spoke to me more than my own coach
did. I asked him what I was doing wrong,

00:12:18.260 --> 00:12:21.460
what I needed to change,
what I was doing well,

00:12:21.660 --> 00:12:24.700
and what I wasn't doing well.
Co Adriaanse was like a soldier.

00:12:24.940 --> 00:12:27.740
He didn't talk much,
he didn't point out mistakes.

00:12:27.940 --> 00:12:32.300
He ran training sessions
in an 11-versus-11 format,

00:12:35.262 --> 00:12:41.780
and if someone stood still,
they were punished with ten push-ups.

00:12:41.980 --> 00:12:45.942
You had to be moving all the time.

00:12:46.180 --> 00:12:55.801
It reminded me of my time in Malmö,
when I was treated differently as well.

00:12:56.620 --> 00:13:00.859
I was constantly being punished.
If I got tired and stopped for a moment,

00:13:01.073 --> 00:13:04.473
ten push-ups followed and it was
always me who got punished.

00:13:05.211 --> 00:13:09.571
It felt as if he was against me.
For a while, I didn't play at all,

00:13:09.749 --> 00:13:13.349
others played instead.
It was challenging for me.

00:13:13.511 --> 00:13:17.255
After three months, I called Malmö
and begged them to buy me back

00:13:17.454 --> 00:13:21.774
because I wanted to return. They told
me they no longer had the money...

00:13:22.074 --> 00:13:29.434
That was just an excuse. They had their
own reasons for not wanting me back.

00:13:29.640 --> 00:13:31.533
I kept fighting at Ajax.

00:13:32.970 --> 00:13:40.299
There was another Greek striker,
Machlas. -Right.

00:13:41.140 --> 00:13:44.580
It was either him or me
for the number nine position.

00:13:44.860 --> 00:13:48.020
Ajax had a system, either the number nine
or the number eleven, the seven,

00:13:48.260 --> 00:13:53.500
the six, the two, the three,
the five, the eight, the ten,

00:13:53.700 --> 00:13:57.860
and the number nine playing behind.
At Ajax we learned

00:13:58.140 --> 00:14:02.260
that you are not a central striker,
you are not in... How do you say...

00:14:02.500 --> 00:14:07.020
In the middle. There are numbers.
They taught you numbers. -...numbers.

00:14:07.220 --> 00:14:10.180
Yes, nine. You are
number nine. You seven.

00:14:10.420 --> 00:14:13.660
You are eleven. Number ten.
That is the "Fankal" school.

00:14:13.900 --> 00:14:18.340
They taught you numbers and
they don't move from that.

00:14:18.540 --> 00:14:22.410
Number nine, you are right,
defence, right.

00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:29.620
Left, six, three, five, eight.
That's how they work.

00:14:30.060 --> 00:14:33.020
That's what I learned there.

00:14:34.220 --> 00:14:40.860
I wasn't playing, I started...
-Warming up. -I was warming up.

00:14:41.940 --> 00:14:49.460
The crowd started chanting
Machlas's name. Already then.

00:14:50.020 --> 00:14:55.341
Mentally, everyone is against me.
I don't speak the language,

00:14:55.700 --> 00:15:00.220
I have a coach who doesn't talk
to me. It kept going like that.

00:15:00.500 --> 00:15:05.220
After ten months, we are first,
first in the league. After ten...

00:15:05.660 --> 00:15:14.500
Not ten. The season lasts ten months.
It was seven, in February.

00:15:15.100 --> 00:15:19.380
They fired Co Adriaanse.
They kicked him out. We were first.

00:15:19.620 --> 00:15:24.140
Koeman comes. Co Adriaanse
did not talk to players.

00:15:24.340 --> 00:15:33.340
He was very strange. He had
rules like we were in the army.

00:15:33.700 --> 00:15:37.340
You couldn't feel football,
there was too much military discipline.

00:15:37.580 --> 00:15:42.340
We were all kids and talented.
The best talents in one team.

00:15:42.660 --> 00:15:48.220
So we need to learn something,
grow, we have potential to be wow.

00:15:48.460 --> 00:15:53.260
But it's all school. OK.
You also need some dialogue.

00:15:53.500 --> 00:15:56.340
Like I said before,
you have to talk to players.

00:15:56.580 --> 00:16:01.660
I am here now, not in Sweden.
I don't have mom, dad, sister, brother.

00:16:01.860 --> 00:16:04.380
I have no one, I am alone.
-You are everything to me.

00:16:04.580 --> 00:16:07.820
I have no one to talk to.
The coach doesn't talk to me.

00:16:08.340 --> 00:16:11.540
Ben Acker understood that.
He fired Co Adriaanse

00:16:11.780 --> 00:16:15.020
and brought Koeman.
Everything started changing.

00:16:15.220 --> 00:16:18.420
Koeman talks to me.
Still, I didn't play.

00:16:18.660 --> 00:16:28.660
I wasn't... How do you say?
-Ready. -Ready for that league.

00:16:29.140 --> 00:16:33.660
Ajax is special, because they play
in a way others don't.

00:16:35.340 --> 00:16:42.180
Everything is programmed.
-Better to be in their school and grow.

00:16:42.420 --> 00:16:45.900
Everyone who comes
to the school can play.

00:16:46.860 --> 00:16:51.860
They gave me... How do you say?
-A pencil. -A pencil.

00:16:52.220 --> 00:16:59.340
They gave me a pencil and showed me.
They put the pencil on paper and say:

00:16:59.740 --> 00:17:04.300
This is number nine, this is number ten.
Number nine goes to the near post,

00:17:04.580 --> 00:17:09.820
number ten goes to the far post.
Same when pressing in midfield.

00:17:10.060 --> 00:17:13.980
When number nine presses him,
number ten goes there. Just with a pencil.

00:17:14.094 --> 00:17:16.534
Everything is drawn.
-Everything is drawn, programmed.

00:17:16.672 --> 00:17:18.392
That's how it is everywhere today.

00:17:18.900 --> 00:17:25.820
I understood that, but I still didn't
play because my confidence dropped.

00:17:26.860 --> 00:17:33.820
We played the cup final in Rotterdam.
I didn't play, but Koeman put me in.

00:17:36.020 --> 00:17:40.940
Last 5-10 minutes, we go into stoppage
time. Back then there was golden goal.

00:17:41.180 --> 00:17:44.740
Whoever scores in extra time
wins. I score the goal.

00:17:44.980 --> 00:17:50.780
That's where the change comes.
I say that in football small details

00:17:50.925 --> 00:17:53.762
change the situation.
-They make a big difference.

00:17:53.962 --> 00:17:56.840
As a striker, if you score one
goal, the situation changes.

00:17:57.088 --> 00:18:00.408
But if you don't score for a long
time and in many matches,

00:18:01.180 --> 00:18:05.340
it doesn't take much to change
your rhythm. I score a goal.

00:18:05.540 --> 00:18:10.821
The next year there was talk
that I would go play in Italy.

00:18:13.100 --> 00:18:17.540
Ajax wasn't sure if I
was a good investment.

00:18:17.780 --> 00:18:26.228
They wanted to get rid of me.
I stayed because Ben Acker was...

00:18:26.660 --> 00:18:33.820
With you. -Yes. He protected me and said
I was good and they need to push me.

00:18:34.140 --> 00:18:39.620
We'll give him more time.
The next year was much better.

00:18:39.860 --> 00:18:45.940
Van Basten arrived. -Yes. -When I started
playing. He gave me... How do you say?

00:18:46.180 --> 00:18:55.115
Advice. -How to play. He told me
I can help the team best

00:18:55.756 --> 00:19:02.460
if I score goals. Everything else
is just play. As a striker.

00:19:03.020 --> 00:19:06.540
The best way to help your team
is to score goals.

00:19:08.260 --> 00:19:15.060
I'll go back to what I want to say.
After that I came to Juventus.

00:19:15.300 --> 00:19:20.340
I saw Capello.
Capello has a different mentality.

00:19:20.540 --> 00:19:25.020
Capello influenced Van Basten.
Van Basten did not learn at Ajax

00:19:25.220 --> 00:19:32.300
that you help the team by scoring goals.
In Ajax they do not teach you this.

00:19:32.540 --> 00:19:36.740
How do you say? -They don't teach you.
-They don't teach you that mentality.

00:19:36.980 --> 00:19:40.660
That was Capello's work. -Capello?
-Capello taught that to Van Basten.

00:19:40.860 --> 00:19:45.420
He no longer played, he was a coach.
Then he told me that.

00:19:45.620 --> 00:19:52.100
Capello told me: The first thing
I will teach you is that I need

00:19:52.540 --> 00:19:59.020
to remove the Ajax system from you.
How they play. I don't play like that.

00:19:59.460 --> 00:20:05.220
You need to score goals, you are a striker
and I will teach you how to score goals.

00:20:05.460 --> 00:20:11.100
For six months he put me in front
of goal, every day, to shoot.

00:20:11.340 --> 00:20:16.992
I shot fifty times, sixty times.
When we finished training,

00:20:17.343 --> 00:20:23.820
we would enter the tunnel to shower.
I went last with Cannavaro,

00:20:24.554 --> 00:20:30.500
and he calls me: Ibra! I have to
go back, to shoot. To train.

00:20:30.700 --> 00:20:33.740
The next day, I wanted to escape,
but I'd hear: "Ibra!"

00:20:33.940 --> 00:20:38.398
And it went on like that for six months.
Then I became a goal-scoring machine.

00:20:38.597 --> 00:20:41.156
That's why Van Basten said:

00:20:41.332 --> 00:20:44.892
"He didn't learn that at Ajax,
he learned it from Fabio Capello."

00:20:45.076 --> 00:20:46.643
That was the difference.

00:20:46.818 --> 00:20:53.018
When he pointed out how I trained
with Kuman, with Co Adriaanse,

00:20:53.300 --> 00:20:55.900
and how I scored goals…
It's important that I score goals,

00:20:56.140 --> 00:21:00.700
but even more important that there's a link
between me, the ten, the seven,

00:21:00.900 --> 00:21:02.700
and the eleven. -Yes, yes.

00:21:02.980 --> 00:21:06.420
And there it was: one touch, two touches,
one touch, two touches…

00:21:06.700 --> 00:21:10.020
And it works well for the game.
-It becomes fluid.

00:21:10.220 --> 00:21:13.580
It's fluid, it moves fast,
and whoever can play one-touch,

00:21:13.860 --> 00:21:17.620
it's a completely different situation.

00:21:18.100 --> 00:21:22.180
That's what I learned back then.
The next year was even better with Kuman.

00:21:22.380 --> 00:21:27.620
I played more, but I wasn't
considered a top prospect yet.

00:21:27.900 --> 00:21:32.020
Then, in the third year,
everything started to take off.

00:21:37.060 --> 00:21:40.740
I met Mino. -That's exactly
what I wanted to ask you.

00:21:41.020 --> 00:21:46.940
He had approached me before.
At first, I was against having an agent.

00:21:47.140 --> 00:21:54.620
I thought they were only interested
in money, not in the player.

00:21:54.940 --> 00:21:58.740
I thought he just wanted
to make a deal for himself.

00:21:58.940 --> 00:22:03.580
I had that image of agents.
-In general. -Yes.

00:22:03.709 --> 00:22:05.749
When I was at Malmö,
everyone wanted me,

00:22:05.872 --> 00:22:09.696
but I didn't give anyone
the chance to get close to me.

00:22:09.818 --> 00:22:11.508
You didn't let them…

00:22:11.660 --> 00:22:15.740
The contract between Malmö and
Ajax I handled without an agent.

00:22:16.580 --> 00:22:19.740
I understand. -Who got paid more?
Malmö, not me.

00:22:19.862 --> 00:22:23.022
I had the worst contract at Ajax.
-That messed you up a bit, right?

00:22:23.145 --> 00:22:28.265
A lot. Totally. And when I realized
they had screwed me over,

00:22:28.740 --> 00:22:31.980
I told myself: "I need an agent."

00:22:32.300 --> 00:22:36.260
Mino had approached me
a year earlier, and I told him:

00:22:36.500 --> 00:22:39.860
"When you have an offer,
then you can come."

00:22:40.060 --> 00:22:47.580
And he sent a message through Max:
"He can go and fuck himself."

00:22:47.780 --> 00:22:51.500
That was an arrogant response
to my arrogance. Fair enough.

00:22:51.660 --> 00:23:00.674
And after a year, I was looking for an agent
and I asked a journalist who had helped me:

00:23:00.838 --> 00:23:07.025
"Listen, I need an agent, but I don't
know how this world works."

00:23:07.405 --> 00:23:11.978
He told me: "You have two options.
One is Beckham's agent,

00:23:12.180 --> 00:23:16.940
part of the London agency IMG
or something like that,

00:23:17.340 --> 00:23:22.060
or the other one, who in my opinion
is better for you.

00:23:22.246 --> 00:23:29.254
He's not Mafia, but he's in that world.
And for your style, he's better."

00:23:29.570 --> 00:23:33.020
That's how I met Mino,
who told them what I had said

00:23:33.221 --> 00:23:35.941
a year earlier when he
first approached me.

00:23:36.133 --> 00:23:39.371
But, so you came back.
That's a good sign.

00:23:39.940 --> 00:23:44.020
When I first saw him, he was like
a character from The Sopranos.

00:23:44.126 --> 00:23:45.975
Do you remember The Sopranos?
-Yes, of course.

00:23:46.170 --> 00:23:48.610
The short guy with the big belly…

00:23:48.834 --> 00:23:56.598
And I showed up in a Porsche,
bought a new Rolex to impress him.

00:23:58.060 --> 00:24:06.220
And he came in a regular Nike t-shirt
and pants and said:

00:24:07.426 --> 00:24:09.506
"Let's go eat sushi."

00:24:09.833 --> 00:24:13.349
He ordered food for five people
just to make sure he ate enough.

00:24:13.569 --> 00:24:21.320
I don't eat much, I was waiting
to see his reaction.

00:24:22.090 --> 00:24:28.505
Then he presented four
different documents for four players.

00:24:29.340 --> 00:24:34.660
The first was David Trezeguet:
27 matches, 20 goals.

00:24:34.900 --> 00:24:38.660
Bobo Vieri: 23 matches, 20 goals.

00:24:39.060 --> 00:24:43.780
Then Inzaghi, and all
the top strikers in Italy.

00:24:44.020 --> 00:24:47.780
Italy at that time was…
-Serie A was number one. -Top.

00:24:48.060 --> 00:24:53.820
Then he pulled out my document:
Ibra, 27 matches, 3 goals.

00:24:54.180 --> 00:24:58.940
Then he asked me, "Who would
buy you with these numbers?"

00:24:59.380 --> 00:25:04.340
I quickly came back and said:
"If I had numbers like these others,

00:25:04.471 --> 00:25:07.704
I wouldn't need an agent.
Even my mom could sell me.

00:25:08.227 --> 00:25:14.731
I need an agent because of
these numbers." He laughed and said:

00:25:15.004 --> 00:25:22.180
"You're right. You need a miracle."
On the way home, he told me:

00:25:22.700 --> 00:25:30.876
"Don't think I'm impressed
by your car or your watch.

00:25:31.053 --> 00:25:34.920
That tells me nothing. These
numbers tell me everything."

00:25:35.862 --> 00:25:40.264
When I got home,
four hours later, I called him

00:25:40.650 --> 00:25:43.826
and said I wanted to start working together,
and he told me to take my time.

00:25:44.550 --> 00:25:49.841
"Take a day or two," he said.

00:25:51.249 --> 00:25:56.318
He already knew I had made up my mind,
but he was provoking me by saying that.

00:25:56.681 --> 00:26:00.879
I told him I didn't need to think because
I knew what I wanted: to start immediately.

00:26:01.012 --> 00:26:03.830
"From now on, everything will be
your problem, not mine."

00:26:04.580 --> 00:26:10.780
When he started training me,
he took everything I had.

00:26:11.020 --> 00:26:14.420
He took my Porsche
and drove it to his house.

00:26:14.660 --> 00:26:17.620
He also took all my watches.

00:26:17.940 --> 00:26:23.940
He gave me a Fiat Stilo,
which was popular at the time.

00:26:24.220 --> 00:26:30.220
He told me that from now on,
I should only walk around in a tracksuit.

00:26:30.500 --> 00:26:36.795
Whoever comes from geto, you have
only the tracksuit and nothing else.

00:26:36.943 --> 00:26:41.428
And that was fine with me,
but I didn't like that he took my Porsche.

00:26:43.260 --> 00:26:50.700
Where I come from Rosengård Malmö,
if you drive a nice car,

00:26:51.860 --> 00:27:00.340
it's proof that you've made it.
-It's a measure of success.

00:27:00.620 --> 00:27:04.780
He humiliated me as
if I hadn't achieved anything.

00:27:05.020 --> 00:27:08.260
But it was okay, I had respect
and I didn't say anything.

00:27:08.500 --> 00:27:13.660
He told me: "Now you're going to
train double because of what you did."

00:27:14.820 --> 00:27:21.180
Everything you've done so far is zero.
Zero! Now you'll start training.

00:27:21.380 --> 00:27:27.740
I want you to suffer.
After every training session,

00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:32.460
I want you to be in a position
where you can't breathe.

00:27:32.620 --> 00:27:37.580
To break boundaries? -Yes.
-And he took everything from me.

00:27:38.340 --> 00:27:41.100
He said:"You'll come
to my mother's place."

00:27:41.380 --> 00:27:47.885
He lived 25 minutes from Amsterdam,
in Haarlem. Maxwell was already there.

00:27:48.012 --> 00:27:50.092
Maxwell and I were together a lot.

00:27:50.300 --> 00:27:56.820
You'll come to my mother's place
and she'll give you something to eat.

00:27:57.100 --> 00:28:05.260
I lived alone and went to IKEA
for meatballs and… Mashed...

00:28:06.300 --> 00:28:08.180
Mashed potatoes, yeah.

00:28:08.500 --> 00:28:11.700
I ate there, because it was
close to the stadium.

00:28:11.940 --> 00:28:20.820
I didn't know how to cook at home.
When I met Mino, I ate there.

00:28:23.460 --> 00:28:28.020
That's where we trained, and after
three months he sold me to Juventus.

00:28:28.260 --> 00:28:30.660
Do you know what's strange about you?

00:28:31.340 --> 00:28:35.620
What surprises me is that people…
And I follow football all the time…

00:28:35.860 --> 00:28:41.180
People think you have an ego and you do,
you're confident and ego-driven.

00:28:41.420 --> 00:28:46.530
People get the impression
that you're the type of guy

00:28:46.655 --> 00:28:48.655
who says "my way or high way."

00:28:49.020 --> 00:28:54.140
Usually people like that surround
themselves with "yes, sir" types.

00:28:54.349 --> 00:28:57.936
But you chose Mino,
who wouldn't say "yes, sir" to you,

00:28:58.129 --> 00:29:02.569
but instead told you:
"No Porsches and no watches."

00:29:02.715 --> 00:29:07.608
You look for someone who will
challenge you? -Yes, exactly.

00:29:07.717 --> 00:29:09.997
Someone who will fight you.

00:29:10.136 --> 00:29:15.490
Someone who says "yes, yes, yes"
is worthless. You have to fight me.

00:29:15.930 --> 00:29:23.045
That's how you earn my respect
and my loyalty. -Loyalty.

00:29:23.226 --> 00:29:26.106
I'll be with you forever.

00:29:26.277 --> 00:29:31.490
That's why I say, I have barriers,
but once you earn my respect…

00:29:32.033 --> 00:29:33.633
Then it's bingo.

00:29:33.780 --> 00:29:37.537
Mino and I did big things,
a big transfer.

00:29:37.745 --> 00:29:43.145
We worked together for over
20 years without a contract.

00:29:44.243 --> 00:29:46.283
Without a contract? -Yes.

00:29:47.100 --> 00:29:51.140
He told me: "The moment
one of us loses trust in the other,

00:29:51.380 --> 00:29:54.220
we'll end the cooperation."
-Do you miss him?

00:29:54.500 --> 00:29:57.780
Once I got angry at him
and we fought a lot.

00:29:58.000 --> 00:30:00.740
There were no hugs,
just a lot of arguments.

00:30:01.020 --> 00:30:08.500
For a match at Ajax, he called
me after I scored two goals.

00:30:08.780 --> 00:30:10.380
Thought I was the best.

00:30:10.620 --> 00:30:16.180
He said: "You were the worst today.
If you hit one more time…"

00:30:16.420 --> 00:30:21.260
The advertising board, yeah.

00:30:23.500 --> 00:30:26.420
"I'll make sure you never
play football again.

00:30:26.620 --> 00:30:31.020
That wasn't okay. You were
the worst player on the pitch.

00:30:31.220 --> 00:30:34.900
The coach should have substituted
you in the first half, not the second."

00:30:35.140 --> 00:30:39.660
He attacked me. And I told him: "Listen,
you don't work for me anymore!"

00:30:39.860 --> 00:30:43.380
He said: "If you fire me,
you have to hire me!

00:30:46.138 --> 00:30:49.366
Did you understand me?" -I did.

00:30:49.780 --> 00:30:54.855
That's how he got on my nerves,
but he knew what he was doing.

00:30:55.208 --> 00:31:01.048
None of it was personal, he was just
motivating and challenging me.

00:31:01.100 --> 00:31:03.540
To raise me to a higher level…

00:31:03.780 --> 00:31:10.921
Like I said, a coach has to get
into a player's head and train him there.

00:31:11.832 --> 00:31:14.818
That's it. -Knowing the details.

00:31:15.056 --> 00:31:19.624
He got into my head and knew
everything. He knew exactly what to do.

00:31:19.756 --> 00:31:23.827
Do you miss him? -A lot.
-Even today? -A lot.

00:31:24.272 --> 00:31:32.077
He was my best friend. I can't say father,
because Šefik is my father.

00:31:32.351 --> 00:31:34.831
He was like family to me.

00:31:35.079 --> 00:31:42.439
He knew all my… -Secrets.
-He knew my entire life.

00:31:44.060 --> 00:31:48.841
When I met Helena, my wife,
he told me: "She will be your wife."

00:31:48.981 --> 00:31:50.661
From the very first day…

00:31:52.300 --> 00:31:54.580
He was everything to me.

00:31:56.340 --> 00:32:02.380
I wish he were still with me
because of Maximillian and Vincent.

00:32:05.580 --> 00:32:09.660
To protect them? -Yes.
I know what football is like.

00:32:12.820 --> 00:32:18.215
He was a complete package
in the world he worked in.

00:32:19.620 --> 00:32:24.860
He sold me to Milan the first time.

00:32:25.260 --> 00:32:29.020
The next day, I was supposed to do
a presentation at the stadium,

00:32:29.300 --> 00:32:36.628
…80,000 people. At halftime,
I was supposed to enter the match.

00:32:37.026 --> 00:32:38.867
He wasn't there.

00:32:39.140 --> 00:32:43.740
The next day, he went with another
one of his players, a 15-year-old,

00:32:43.980 --> 00:32:47.460
to look for an apartment for him.

00:32:48.380 --> 00:32:54.179
That's the kind of person he was.
He didn't seek glamour or fame.

00:32:54.475 --> 00:32:56.287
He worked for the player.

00:32:56.483 --> 00:32:59.507
"My player is my child.
I work for the player."

00:32:59.700 --> 00:33:02.340
That's why he argued with clubs.

00:33:02.580 --> 00:33:05.820
He said: "I don't work for the club.
I work for the player.

00:33:06.020 --> 00:33:11.500
The player is my asset, not the club.
You have to pay if you want my player.

00:33:11.740 --> 00:33:15.300
If you don't want him, no problem.
I don't work for the club."

00:33:15.580 --> 00:33:20.020
That's why everyone was against him,
but he gave everything for his players.

00:33:20.260 --> 00:33:23.580
That's how he was.
He died very young.

00:33:23.940 --> 00:33:30.060
Of course, with some players
he was closer than with others.

00:33:30.260 --> 00:33:34.620
That's natural. He spent
a lot of time with me.

00:33:34.860 --> 00:33:38.540
And Maxwell was his too, like me.

00:33:38.940 --> 00:33:46.620
He was with us more than with his own
two sons. -Yes. That's how it was.

00:33:46.860 --> 00:33:49.300
And it all passed too quickly.
Far too quickly.

00:33:49.500 --> 00:33:53.900
﻿Alright, he took you to Juve.
That was a big step.

00:33:54.180 --> 00:33:57.260
You yourself said that at that
time Serie A...

00:33:57.460 --> 00:33:59.860
And Juventus is one of
the biggest clubs in Europe.

00:34:00.100 --> 00:34:04.220
And anyway, The Old Lady,
Vecchia Signora... -Yes.

00:34:04.540 --> 00:34:07.540
The club is organized
a bit like the army, right?

00:34:07.740 --> 00:34:13.580
It was a bit, scary.
-A bit scary.

00:34:13.940 --> 00:34:18.260
At Ajax, I was considered
a talented player.

00:34:18.500 --> 00:34:23.580
Talented and with the potential
for... -Yes, you were talented.

00:34:24.380 --> 00:34:30.260
After playing in Ajax,
I moved to Juventus.

00:34:30.660 --> 00:34:35.100
When I entered the locker room...
-You entered the locker room.

00:34:35.460 --> 00:34:40.580
I saw players like Trezeguet,
Cannavaro, Thuram... -Del Piero.

00:34:40.820 --> 00:34:46.980
...Del Piero, Buffon, Emerson, Nedved.

00:34:47.660 --> 00:34:49.620
I said to myself,
this is not possible.

00:34:49.820 --> 00:34:53.380
Just a week earlier, when I was
at Ajax with my friends,

00:34:53.580 --> 00:34:58.460
playing PlayStation there were
names I saw in the lockeroom.

00:34:58.700 --> 00:35:03.020
For me, all of it felt
like science fiction.

00:35:04.540 --> 00:35:08.270
I thought... -Like you were dreaming.
-Is everything I’m seeing real? -Yes.

00:35:08.420 --> 00:35:10.860
Am I maybe dreaming?
-It felt like a dream.

00:35:11.660 --> 00:35:15.380
When I came the next day,
I saw the same players.

00:35:15.660 --> 00:35:20.620
Then I knew everything was real.
And I became part of that team.

00:35:21.060 --> 00:35:24.300
If you remember, I told you earlier
that I have confidence.

00:35:24.580 --> 00:35:28.100
When I step on the pitch,
I feel alive.

00:35:29.620 --> 00:35:31.601
I become someone else,
I don't look like this, like I do now.

00:35:31.712 --> 00:35:33.718
If we played football,
you would understand.

00:35:33.874 --> 00:35:36.226
Either you will hate me
or you will love me.

00:35:36.376 --> 00:35:39.576
Either I lift you up,
or you’ll have to…

00:35:39.808 --> 00:35:43.488
There were many players
who cried because of me.

00:35:43.774 --> 00:35:46.976
Because when I start applying
pressure during the game...

00:35:47.308 --> 00:35:51.007
Yes, I know what you mean.
-Then football is no longer a game for me.

00:35:51.184 --> 00:35:55.429
Players like Rebić and others
who played with me can confirm that.

00:35:55.555 --> 00:35:59.421
While I'm on the pitch,
I'm not screwing around.

00:35:59.764 --> 00:36:03.764
If we train for just one hour,
then we really train for one hour.

00:36:04.044 --> 00:36:08.244
After that hour is over,
we can joke around and socialize.

00:36:08.740 --> 00:36:13.420
But when we train, we really train.
That's why, when I'm in training...

00:36:13.662 --> 00:36:15.867
Many players wonder why
Zlatan plays so aggressively.

00:36:16.080 --> 00:36:20.383
I go into duels, I dribble, I score goals.
I remember once when Thuram...

00:36:23.860 --> 00:36:29.580
You know, in older versions
of boots there were six... -Studs.

00:36:29.780 --> 00:36:33.060
But six. -Yes, there were six.
-Today it's a mix. -That's right.

00:36:33.700 --> 00:36:39.700
And those... I watched Thuram
training in boots like that.

00:36:39.900 --> 00:36:42.500
Normally, you only use
those boots in matches.

00:36:42.700 --> 00:36:46.727
In training, you use boots
with rubber studs. -That’s right.

00:36:47.860 --> 00:36:50.137
When I saw him training in those,
I thought, what is this?

00:36:50.287 --> 00:36:52.325
His first duel in training
was with Del Piero.

00:36:52.570 --> 00:37:00.468
And at that time, Del Piero had
a beard and adidas boots. -That's right.

00:37:00.659 --> 00:37:03.046
And now I’m seeing all of this in training.

00:37:03.281 --> 00:37:06.681
At one moment, when Del Piero
controlled the ball with his chest,

00:37:06.855 --> 00:37:09.895
Thuram hit him from behind.

00:37:10.315 --> 00:37:17.315
So hard that he fell face-first
to the ground, and when he got up,

00:37:17.618 --> 00:37:20.778
he had grass in his mouth.

00:37:21.040 --> 00:37:25.760
Then I thought, if Thuram
did this to Del Piero,

00:37:26.140 --> 00:37:28.820
then he’s going to break my legs.

00:37:29.340 --> 00:37:32.700
After that, I decided that in every
duel I had to go in aggressively.

00:37:32.845 --> 00:37:35.590
Of course, many players
were angry because of that.

00:37:35.752 --> 00:37:38.552
Because some of them
were older than me.

00:37:38.728 --> 00:37:43.688
And the name Ibrahimović at that time
didn’t mean much in world of football.

00:37:44.500 --> 00:37:46.300
Still, I went hard into the duels.

00:37:46.540 --> 00:37:51.540
I had a lot of adrenaline, I ran a lot.
But this time I didn't have

00:37:51.780 --> 00:37:55.182
the same problem as at Ajax.
At Juventus, I was... -Ready.

00:37:55.406 --> 00:37:59.464
I was ready in a different way.
Mentally. I was...

00:37:59.907 --> 00:38:04.787
It's like when you take
a strong first hit,

00:38:05.300 --> 00:38:09.340
and every next one
doesn’t seem as strong.

00:38:09.391 --> 00:38:11.551
You already have experience with it.

00:38:11.713 --> 00:38:17.289
I had experience from Ajax.
-Yes, you had experience.

00:38:17.530 --> 00:38:20.242
I was more... -Ready for it.

00:38:20.492 --> 00:38:24.261
I was truly ready and I told myself
that I wouldn’t wait for anyone anymore.

00:38:24.396 --> 00:38:25.956
I just want to play...

00:38:26.131 --> 00:38:29.291
And in the end, only one can stay.
Either me, or Del Piero, or Trezeguet.

00:38:29.438 --> 00:38:31.918
I want to play and I know
that I'm better than both of them.

00:38:32.080 --> 00:38:34.992
My coach was Capello,
and he wasn't...

00:38:35.372 --> 00:38:39.972
He was an old-school coach.
He stuck to the rules.

00:38:40.361 --> 00:38:44.561
When I arrived for training
on the first day, there was no…

00:38:45.220 --> 00:38:48.260
At that time, Juventus had
only two training pitches.

00:38:48.460 --> 00:38:51.460
Even today, the situation
is not much better.

00:38:51.660 --> 00:38:56.580
Today it looks much more modern.
They’ve built modern training grounds.

00:38:56.860 --> 00:39:05.740
In my time, there were only two pitches
with very little grass. -I understand.

00:39:06.020 --> 00:39:12.300
But the executives didn’t worry about that.
I’ll tell you another story about Moggi.

00:39:12.460 --> 00:39:14.940
Moggi was the director
at that time. -Yes.

00:39:15.220 --> 00:39:19.900
When I arrived at training
on the first day, it was breakfast time.

00:39:20.220 --> 00:39:26.260
Capello was sitting at the table,
reading La Gazzetta dello Sport.

00:39:26.500 --> 00:39:29.980
Those newspapers are pink.
-Yes, they’re pink.

00:39:30.180 --> 00:39:32.860
I thought that was cool.

00:39:33.013 --> 00:39:36.893
Before that, I had only seen them
on TV and on YouTube.

00:39:37.102 --> 00:39:43.982
I had never even heard of that newspaper.
But the color was really cool.

00:39:44.167 --> 00:39:47.487
He was sitting at the table,
and earlier I had already asked

00:39:47.672 --> 00:39:50.392
people at the club how
you address the coach here.

00:39:50.568 --> 00:39:52.288
They told me to say, "mister."

00:39:52.395 --> 00:39:56.681
When I got close to him,
I said, "Buongiorno, mister."

00:39:56.951 --> 00:39:59.353
But he kept on reading the newspaper.

00:39:59.619 --> 00:40:02.861
After ten minutes passed,
I started wondering if

00:40:03.020 --> 00:40:09.100
maybe I had said something wrong.
The situation wasn’t clear to me.

00:40:09.300 --> 00:40:13.940
Or maybe he hadn’t heard or seen me.
After ten minutes, he put the newspaper

00:40:14.140 --> 00:40:21.090
down and left the room. I thought
I had done something wrong.

00:40:21.690 --> 00:40:27.570
I went into the locker room
and asked the guys

00:40:27.780 --> 00:40:30.260
if the coach
had a problem with me, or...

00:40:30.516 --> 00:40:35.184
I even wondered if the issue was my
English, because I wasn't so go at it...

00:40:35.761 --> 00:40:39.401
They told me not to worry,
that everything was fine.

00:40:39.618 --> 00:40:43.018
After three months,
I got to know Capello better

00:40:43.460 --> 00:40:48.005
and asked him how he works
with a group of players like that,

00:40:48.740 --> 00:40:54.215
how he earns their respect, because
the squad was full of personalities...

00:40:54.284 --> 00:40:57.472
Nedved... -Strong characters, yes.
-Everyone was full of confidence,

00:40:57.583 --> 00:41:00.550
everyone thought they were the best
in the world, and in truth, they were.

00:41:00.808 --> 00:41:04.964
He then told me, "I don't
ask for respect. I take it."

00:41:05.560 --> 00:41:11.605
That's the difference.
I don't ask for respect, I take it.

00:41:12.500 --> 00:41:15.700
What he did to me on
the very first day was exactly that:

00:41:15.863 --> 00:41:19.641
he took my respect by
not answering me. -Yes, yes.

00:41:19.780 --> 00:41:24.020
He put me in my place immediately.
-Straight away...

00:41:24.241 --> 00:41:26.595
Immediately, on the first day.

00:41:26.940 --> 00:41:29.100
He was the one who wanted
me to come to Juventus,

00:41:29.340 --> 00:41:32.100
he was the one who
brought me there to play.

00:41:32.300 --> 00:41:35.100
On my first day, I arrived and said,
"Buongiorno, mister,"

00:41:35.380 --> 00:41:38.260
and with that single moment alone
he put me exactly where I needed to be.

00:41:38.460 --> 00:41:43.420
Bravo, yes... -Small details
that make all the difference.

00:41:43.560 --> 00:41:45.293
But he really was special.

00:41:45.620 --> 00:41:51.140
He picked me up, and then...
-Brought you back down.

00:41:51.380 --> 00:41:56.180
Yes, brought me back down. When it came
to everything connected to Van Basten,

00:41:56.319 --> 00:41:58.879
he told me that the first thing
he would do with me

00:41:59.064 --> 00:42:03.184
was to erase the Ajax systems from me
and that here I had to score goals.

00:42:03.407 --> 00:42:06.247
He said, "If you want to help the team,
here you must score goals.

00:42:06.518 --> 00:42:09.238
You do everything well
until you reach the goal,

00:42:09.463 --> 00:42:15.303
but in front of the goal, nothing happens.
We're going to change that now."

00:42:15.660 --> 00:42:19.540
He said: "Outside the box,
everything is fine,

00:42:19.780 --> 00:42:23.180
but once you enter the box,
you have to be aggressive."

00:42:23.620 --> 00:42:30.740
Then he put on a tape. -A tape?
-A tape with Van Basten's goals.

00:42:30.940 --> 00:42:38.300
He said, "You are Van Basten,"
or somewhat similar... -Similar...

00:42:38.820 --> 00:42:44.353
"Yes, you are similar to Van Basten
in the way you move on the pitch."

00:42:44.557 --> 00:42:46.157
I said to him, "All right."

00:42:46.354 --> 00:42:50.455
He played the tape,
and I watched only Van Basten's goals,

00:42:50.583 --> 00:42:53.143
nothing but goals, only highlights.

00:42:53.384 --> 00:42:55.824
I watched how he turned,
how he scored with his head,

00:42:56.008 --> 00:43:02.168
how he attacked aggressively,
how he fought. It lasted 20 minutes.

00:43:02.511 --> 00:43:06.090
I was alone in that room,
because the training ground

00:43:07.140 --> 00:43:09.275
was old school back then.

00:43:09.441 --> 00:43:12.561
We only had tapes, unlike today where
you have all the modern technology.

00:43:12.776 --> 00:43:14.816
At that time, none of that existed.

00:43:15.260 --> 00:43:19.700
For 20 minutes I was watching that,
and I heard nothing else.

00:43:19.900 --> 00:43:25.300
I was just watching, and I was afraid
that if I left, something would happen.

00:43:25.406 --> 00:43:28.166
I've always had that way of thinking.

00:43:28.382 --> 00:43:32.102
25 minutes pass by, 30 minutes
pass by and I say to myself:

00:43:32.265 --> 00:43:35.165
"Alright, I understand it.
What more does he want from me?"

00:43:35.718 --> 00:43:39.798
I left the room and looked around
to see whether Capello was there.

00:43:40.016 --> 00:43:44.336
I was alone at the training ground;
everyone else had already gone home.

00:43:44.433 --> 00:43:46.384
He had left me there
to study those movements

00:43:46.498 --> 00:43:48.378
while everyone else
had already gone home.

00:43:48.547 --> 00:43:53.282
I thought it wasn't normal, I kept
asking myself what he was doing to me...

00:43:53.554 --> 00:43:56.514
I was getting irritated
and that was precisely what he wanted.

00:43:56.714 --> 00:44:00.564
He wanted you to be entirely focused.
-Exactly. He wanted me to change.

00:44:00.693 --> 00:44:04.413
For six months, he assigned his
assistant to work with me

00:44:04.550 --> 00:44:07.150
in front of the goal every single day.

00:44:07.360 --> 00:44:11.696
Young players would come in,
like Giovinco and De Sciglio,

00:44:11.861 --> 00:44:14.821
who later played for Juventus.
-They were Primavera players.

00:44:15.023 --> 00:44:19.943
They would pass me balls, and I would
score goals - 50, 60, 70 shots...

00:44:20.300 --> 00:44:23.500
I kept shooting and scoring,
and that assistant kept irritating me.

00:44:23.740 --> 00:44:27.420
Every single time I missed, he would
tell me I would never score a goal.

00:44:27.542 --> 00:44:29.756
He was an older man,
very well known in Italy,

00:44:29.820 --> 00:44:33.340
someone who had worked with Capello,
with Van Basten and others.

00:44:33.479 --> 00:44:36.359
And every time I missed,
he would say the same thing.

00:44:36.489 --> 00:44:38.951
It annoyed me, but that's something I've
carried inside me since much earlier:

00:44:39.102 --> 00:44:41.584
when someone attacks me,
it fuels me to play even better.

00:44:41.748 --> 00:44:44.193
I understand, that's clear to me.
He motivated you.

00:44:44.311 --> 00:44:49.209
Yes. He kept telling me: "You're like
Van Basten, but you don't move like him.

00:44:49.357 --> 00:44:51.982
You have a better technique than Van
Basten, but you have to score goals.

00:44:52.076 --> 00:44:55.490
You need to move..." -Timing...
-To move like Van Basten inside the box.

00:44:55.645 --> 00:44:57.843
And that movement was always
forward, forward, forward...

00:44:58.188 --> 00:45:02.054
And in the end, in a way,
he created a monster.

00:45:02.388 --> 00:45:04.868
Because today,
when I step onto the pitch,

00:45:05.015 --> 00:45:07.595
there is only one thing
in my head - I go.

00:45:07.819 --> 00:45:12.508
If you're in front of me, you and the
ball are both going into the goal.

00:45:12.664 --> 00:45:18.235
I understand... -And the goalkeeper with
you as well... That's how he created me.

00:45:18.439 --> 00:45:24.196
He made you that way. -Yes, he created
me like that. He created a monster.

00:45:24.340 --> 00:45:28.140
After that, I just kept pushing forward.

00:45:28.380 --> 00:45:31.900
And then I told Moggi what
I had wanted to mention earlier...

00:45:32.140 --> 00:45:40.220
While we were showering, me, Trezeguet,
Nedved, Camoranesi and the others,

00:45:40.420 --> 00:45:43.100
the water wasn't draining
from the floor.

00:45:43.860 --> 00:45:46.860
I said: "What is this?
This isn't normal, we're Juventus."

00:45:47.060 --> 00:45:50.340
I had a good relationship with Moggi.

00:45:50.658 --> 00:45:55.477
I told him: "Listen, we were showering
and the water wasn't draining.

00:45:55.669 --> 00:45:58.196
What's up with that?
That's not at the Juventus level."

00:45:58.373 --> 00:46:09.453
He replied: "You're not here
to have it good. You're here to win."

00:46:09.680 --> 00:46:12.830
You didn't come here to enjoy yourself,
but... -... to win. -Exactly.

00:46:13.008 --> 00:46:15.851
I understood everything immediately.
-You feel the pressure straight away.

00:46:16.032 --> 00:46:18.140
Exactly. That's why I say
that when you're at Juventus,

00:46:18.298 --> 00:46:20.718
you adopt a different mentality.
You think only about winning.

00:46:20.844 --> 00:46:22.851
That is the Juventus culture.

00:46:22.965 --> 00:46:27.374
Anyone who has been through Juventus
speaks differently compared to those

00:46:27.484 --> 00:46:29.781
who played for Milan or Inter.

00:46:30.193 --> 00:46:33.030
I understand, and we'll definitely
talk more about that.

00:46:33.115 --> 00:46:35.077
It's a different mentality.

00:46:35.201 --> 00:46:38.054
He told me clearly: "You're not here to
enjoy yourself. You're here to win."

00:46:38.183 --> 00:46:42.093
He put me in my place immediately.
Capello taught me respect,

00:46:42.544 --> 00:46:46.024
and Moggi instilled
the Juventus mentality in me.

00:46:46.193 --> 00:46:53.147
Capello transformed me in terms of what
matters on the pitch - scoring goals.

00:46:53.432 --> 00:46:56.392
And then there's another player
you mentioned.

00:46:56.607 --> 00:47:02.567
You have Moggi, Capello,
you also point out Vieira. -Vieira.

00:47:02.659 --> 00:47:04.686
He arrived in the second year.

00:47:04.824 --> 00:47:09.224
Did he have that same mentality?
-He arrived in the second year.

00:47:09.589 --> 00:47:14.829
Back then he won the World Cup,
he played for Arsenal.

00:47:15.022 --> 00:47:20.342
Then he joined us. Back then,
big players didn't change clubs often.

00:47:20.581 --> 00:47:25.141
They stayed for a long time. He had already
been at Arsenal for 9-10 years. -Surely.

00:47:25.326 --> 00:47:30.406
He arrived as a big name.
He was different from the others.

00:47:30.740 --> 00:47:36.707
The others, it's not that
they attacked me, but...

00:47:39.820 --> 00:47:45.540
They looked at me like a kid.
You have time, you need to learn,

00:47:45.780 --> 00:47:51.940
but I was persistent anyway.
Then Vieira arrived. He pushed me.

00:47:52.180 --> 00:47:56.620
Differently than the others. He told me I
could do much better than what I was doing.

00:47:56.820 --> 00:48:02.500
What you're doing is 10%, it's not enough.
You need to work more. He provoked me.

00:48:04.688 --> 00:48:13.010
He started attacking me on the pitch.
When I would press a player,

00:48:13.226 --> 00:48:19.445
he would talk back and challenge me.
-Yes. -The respect grew like this.

00:48:19.660 --> 00:48:24.500
Two heads who want to win, but not
only in the game, but at training too.

00:48:24.700 --> 00:48:31.140
He "lifted" me even more. When someone
asks who is the best player I played with,

00:48:31.700 --> 00:48:38.700
I always mention him. I played with
Messi, Ronaldinho and others.

00:48:38.940 --> 00:48:45.780
But, who made me better?
-Who made you better.

00:48:46.060 --> 00:48:49.860
Who pushed you... Him, right?
-The others were names.

00:48:50.060 --> 00:48:54.500
They didn't make me better,
he did. That's why I always say

00:48:54.700 --> 00:49:03.940
that Vieira was the player who pushed me.
The way I play... -Like a mindset.

00:49:04.300 --> 00:49:06.540
Not only in games, but at training too.

00:49:06.780 --> 00:49:15.780
You mentioned that Mido was at Ajax,
then Trezeguet, Del Piero.

00:49:15.980 --> 00:49:24.449
Then Crespo, Adriano, then Messi,
Henry. Cavani, Rooney, is that right?

00:49:26.260 --> 00:49:30.100
Is it possible to develop a friendship
between two players

00:49:30.300 --> 00:49:35.580
or is it more competition? Strikers are
sensitive. -Competition will always exist.

00:49:35.780 --> 00:49:40.100
Whoever says there isn't,
that we're friends. Competition.

00:49:40.300 --> 00:49:45.740
One has a bigger ego than the other.
You have your character.

00:49:45.980 --> 00:49:52.260
Then there is the style of your play.
-Yes. -If we talk about Cavani.

00:49:52.408 --> 00:49:56.568
He is a player who needs goals.
If he doesn't score, he doesn't feel good.

00:49:56.823 --> 00:50:03.383
I... I loved to move on the pitch,
to play and score goals.

00:50:03.740 --> 00:50:09.580
Also to assist. It was
difficult for him in Paris.

00:50:09.820 --> 00:50:14.620
I was the center forward, number nine,
and they put him at position eleven.

00:50:14.860 --> 00:50:20.740
I told him, because I didn't have
an ego to be the best.

00:50:20.980 --> 00:50:27.935
I'll show you how I play.
I tell him to move into the middle.

00:50:28.386 --> 00:50:37.349
I'll give you space and I'll turn around.
When I talk to young kids,

00:50:38.090 --> 00:50:42.325
I ask them when they get in front
of the keeper, just the two of you.

00:50:42.582 --> 00:50:47.371
You have the ball in front of the keeper.
Do you score or do you assist?

00:50:47.556 --> 00:50:52.316
What will you do? That way I immediately
find out what kind of player they are.

00:50:52.540 --> 00:50:56.860
If he tells me he will score the goal.
That's not the right answer.

00:50:57.060 --> 00:51:01.820
If he tells me he'll assist,
that's a player. -Šuker would score.

00:51:02.206 --> 00:51:08.021
Then he's not a player for me.
For me, the one who assists is better

00:51:08.225 --> 00:51:11.985
to the one who scores,
and that makes this player better.

00:51:12.170 --> 00:51:17.650
More of a team player, OK. -Yes.
Next time he's in that position,

00:51:17.920 --> 00:51:22.120
will he pass the ball or not? -I agree.
But on the other hand, true goalscorers...

00:51:22.337 --> 00:51:26.904
You are greater when you pass
to someone else to score.

00:51:27.780 --> 00:51:34.780
When Zidane played, when he stepped on
the pitch, the other ten became like Zidane.

00:51:35.300 --> 00:51:39.580
That was his quality.
He didn't do everything alone.

00:51:39.780 --> 00:51:44.700
He did everything so everyone else
would be Zidane. -100%. -That's different.

00:51:44.900 --> 00:51:47.500
That's why I say.
When they're in front of goal,

00:51:47.700 --> 00:51:51.020
players who only score
for themselves are small.

00:51:51.220 --> 00:51:53.740
A great player is one who assists
so someone else can score.

00:51:53.940 --> 00:51:57.500
He has no ego to score
only for himself.

00:51:57.791 --> 00:52:03.311
But you are one of the rare great
goalscorers without a big ego.

00:52:03.609 --> 00:52:08.169
Rooney is like that, right?
But Harry Kane, Šuker...

00:52:08.377 --> 00:52:14.257
I wanted to be complete.
Whoever only thinks of themselves...

00:52:14.489 --> 00:52:18.129
You're like Bokšić. He was like that.
-Bokšić didn't score many goals.

00:52:18.259 --> 00:52:21.179
He's not a goalscorer. Maybe
that's why he didn't score them.

00:52:21.371 --> 00:52:24.651
In those days, players didn't
score many goals. -True.

00:52:24.929 --> 00:52:31.572
Back then, if you scored 8, 9, or 10
goals, it's like 25-30 goals today.

00:52:31.740 --> 00:52:36.900
They didn't score over 20 goals
back then. Times were different.

00:52:37.140 --> 00:52:43.180
For me, he is a greater player when he's in
front of the goal and passes to another.

00:52:43.301 --> 00:52:46.261
He is a greater player than
the one who just wants to score.

00:52:46.413 --> 00:52:48.693
He's more of a team
player, of course.

00:52:48.847 --> 00:52:54.647
Fine. Juve, you win. Two years.
-Two years. -Two titles.

00:52:54.856 --> 00:52:59.696
You are the top scorer. -At training
it was harder than in the matches.

00:52:59.929 --> 00:53:08.529
Training was fierce. -But the Moggi
affair happens, where he is involved.

00:53:08.691 --> 00:53:12.771
What happened was ugly.
I said I didn't want to stay.

00:53:12.893 --> 00:53:16.005
I didn't want to play in Serie B.
-That interests me.

00:53:16.143 --> 00:53:19.543
I wanted to play in the Champions League,
in Serie A. I'm not a player for Serie B.

00:53:19.689 --> 00:53:26.489
And loyalty? -What does that mean?
-Loyalty. Juve, you know?

00:53:26.596 --> 00:53:30.567
You've been there two years,
some players left, some stayed.

00:53:30.760 --> 00:53:34.280
Someone stayed. -Deschamps
wants you to stay, right?

00:53:34.466 --> 00:53:38.386
He wants to build the team with you.
-A lot of players left.

00:53:38.649 --> 00:53:45.249
They tried to... -Retain. -Retain
many players to return to Serie A.

00:53:46.420 --> 00:53:52.540
To me and Mino, it's not about
loyalty. It's about your career.

00:53:52.856 --> 00:53:57.616
Now there is Juventus and Ibrahimović.
What does Ibra want, what does Juve want?

00:53:57.833 --> 00:54:03.433
I want to play at the top, to try to
play in the Champions League.

00:54:03.689 --> 00:54:08.889
If I go there, I will lose a year
in Serie B. -Of course.

00:54:09.096 --> 00:54:11.696
But loyalty is something
completely different.

00:54:11.984 --> 00:54:17.424
And what actually is loyalty?
-Does it even exist in football? -No.

00:54:18.500 --> 00:54:22.660
I thought about it like this:
"I could stay in Malmö,

00:54:22.900 --> 00:54:27.540
with my family, in my hometown,
in my own house, with my friends."

00:54:27.740 --> 00:54:33.580
But I didn’t. I packed my bag and
went to  another city to show who I was.

00:54:33.780 --> 00:54:41.401
And when I’d done everything I could there,
I packed my bag again and moved on,

00:54:41.592 --> 00:54:48.698
to grow - as a person and as a player.
But I never left a club without a reason.

00:54:48.895 --> 00:54:51.947
In Barcelona, it was a 50–50 situation.
That was different.

00:54:52.129 --> 00:54:55.533
The first six months, and the next six.
-Yes, I understand.

00:54:55.769 --> 00:54:59.877
But it wasn’t about football.
It was about something else.

00:55:00.046 --> 00:55:04.807
I wanted to challenge myself,
to play for different clubs,

00:55:05.009 --> 00:55:08.221
to see how good I really was.
If a player stays at one club

00:55:08.384 --> 00:55:11.314
for twenty years,
I respect that deeply.

00:55:12.151 --> 00:55:18.580
But that’s not who I am. I wanted
to test myself in the Premier League,

00:55:18.849 --> 00:55:21.489
La Liga, the French league,
the Italian league…

00:55:22.236 --> 00:55:23.685
Because a career is short.

00:55:23.871 --> 00:55:26.831
To see who I really was,
and to grow - as a player and as a man.

00:55:27.039 --> 00:55:30.799
Because in every country,
football is played differently.

00:55:31.078 --> 00:55:33.598
I agree, but that’s…
that’s how it is.

00:55:33.907 --> 00:55:38.467
When it comes to loyalty,
I agree with you.

00:55:38.722 --> 00:55:43.202
I admire players who stay
at one club their whole…

00:55:43.722 --> 00:55:45.470
Yes. Respect to them.

00:55:45.571 --> 00:55:47.462
But in my opinion,
loyalty should be shown like this:

00:55:47.624 --> 00:55:50.282
while you’re at the club,
you give everything,

00:55:50.453 --> 00:55:53.613
even if you’re injured, if you can,
even if you’re sick.

00:55:53.783 --> 00:55:56.670
You don’t speak against the club.
But when you leave, you leave. -Yes.

00:55:56.840 --> 00:55:59.685
The problem is that fans,
for better or worse, see it differently.

00:56:00.020 --> 00:56:03.580
Fans will always be the same.
-They’re the most loyal. -Always.

00:56:03.900 --> 00:56:07.260
So. You say "no" to Moggi
and you come to Inter.

00:56:07.500 --> 00:56:11.300
A similar club in terms of character.
The players are the same type, right?

00:56:12.180 --> 00:56:13.980
They weren't pussies.

00:56:14.220 --> 00:56:17.820
At that time at Inter,
Moratti was the club president.

00:56:18.060 --> 00:56:21.100
When he gives you a contract,
the rest is up to you.

00:56:23.380 --> 00:56:26.420
The mentality wasn’t
the same as at Juventus.

00:56:26.700 --> 00:56:29.940
Back then, I had to choose
between Inter and Milan.

00:56:30.180 --> 00:56:34.460
I chose Inter because
they worked harder to sign me.

00:56:34.660 --> 00:56:38.300
Inter hadn’t won
the Scudetto for 17 years.

00:56:39.060 --> 00:56:46.020
I was thinking: between Inter and Milan,
where can I create a story if I win?

00:56:46.126 --> 00:56:47.807
Milan had already won
the Champions League.

00:56:47.931 --> 00:56:50.691
You wanted impact. -Yes, impact.
I saw that at Inter there had been

00:56:50.813 --> 00:56:54.807
Baggio, Ronaldo, all the great players,
and they still hadn’t won.

00:56:55.180 --> 00:56:59.140
I said to myself: "If I go there and win,
then it means something."

00:56:59.340 --> 00:57:05.300
It’s on you. -That’s a bigger challenge
for me than going to Milan

00:57:05.540 --> 00:57:07.780
and being just one of those
who had already won.

00:57:07.980 --> 00:57:09.420
They’d already done it.

00:57:09.580 --> 00:57:14.260
I went to Inter for three years,
and we won all three years.

00:57:14.460 --> 00:57:18.860
So the impact was worth it. I did
something that will go down in history,

00:57:19.100 --> 00:57:21.260
and no one can take
that away from you.

00:57:21.460 --> 00:57:25.540
I could have played at Inter, not won
anything, and no one would remember me.

00:57:25.780 --> 00:57:29.500
Instead, I played, I won,
and I left my mark.

00:57:29.700 --> 00:57:33.980
You were the league’s top scorer, right?
-I was the best foreign player,

00:57:34.220 --> 00:57:37.211
the best overall player,
and in the third year, with Mourinho,

00:57:37.424 --> 00:57:41.144
I was also the top scorer.
-Now explain this to me…

00:57:41.282 --> 00:57:46.282
Is it true that when you arrived at Inter,
you realized that Moratti

00:57:47.107 --> 00:57:49.956
was actually the best president
for the players?

00:57:50.182 --> 00:57:53.628
He gives bonuses,
but you told him he shouldn’t do that.

00:57:54.050 --> 00:57:57.330
OK, after we won
the derby against Milan,

00:57:57.586 --> 00:58:01.026
some players told him
that he should give us bonuses.

00:58:01.360 --> 00:58:05.360
Because he had such a big heart,
he gave us bonuses.

00:58:06.340 --> 00:58:09.940
Then I went to him
and asked for the opposite.

00:58:10.180 --> 00:58:14.100
I told him, "Listen, if you want us
to keep winning, this isn’t the way.

00:58:14.340 --> 00:58:20.420
If you give them a bonus for one match,
they’ll lose their hunger to win.

00:58:20.660 --> 00:58:24.300
Because you’ve already fed them
after just one game." -Yes, yes.

00:58:24.540 --> 00:58:28.500
A win against Milan
must not change anything.

00:58:28.780 --> 00:58:33.580
When we win the trophy at the end,
then you can do whatever you want.

00:58:33.820 --> 00:58:39.100
Give bonuses, do everything you like,
because we’ve delivered the result.

00:58:39.700 --> 00:58:45.420
After that, do whatever you want
and everyone will be grateful.

00:58:45.660 --> 00:58:48.660
But you don’t do it after just one match.
That’s not the way. -Bravo!

00:58:48.860 --> 00:58:51.540
We play 38 matches a season.

00:58:51.780 --> 00:58:59.420
In all 38, we have to stay focused
and keep that desire to win.

00:58:59.660 --> 00:59:02.500
That hunger, yes.
-Hunger for victory.

00:59:03.220 --> 00:59:06.460
You don’t start being grateful
after a single win.

00:59:06.660 --> 00:59:10.860
No, no. That’s not the way.
I insisted on that,

00:59:11.380 --> 00:59:14.420
even though the match against Milan
was different, because it was a derby.

00:59:14.620 --> 00:59:17.180
Okay, those are special matches.
It’s a derby.

00:59:17.380 --> 00:59:19.620
But for me, that wasn’t enough.

00:59:19.820 --> 00:59:23.220
You have to win trophies
and enter history.

00:59:23.420 --> 00:59:28.020
When I saw they hadn’t won for
17 years, that was a challenge for me.

00:59:28.300 --> 00:59:31.340
If I can win here with players
who hadn’t won before,

00:59:31.540 --> 00:59:36.020
then it means I’ve done something,
not just for myself,

00:59:36.109 --> 00:59:38.130
but for the whole team,
for the coaches,

00:59:38.286 --> 00:59:40.806
and for everyone working at the club.
But I was the only one

00:59:40.951 --> 00:59:44.364
who could truly say:
we won after I arrived.

00:59:44.506 --> 00:59:47.863
Anyone who comes after that
and wins can’t say the same.

00:59:48.042 --> 00:59:50.269
Because it didn’t happen
just because of them,

00:59:50.440 --> 00:59:54.079
it happened because there was already
a winning machine in place. -Exactly.

00:59:54.187 --> 00:59:56.067
Just like at Barcelona.

00:59:56.420 --> 01:00:00.180
I didn’t go to Barcelona
and make them win.

01:00:00.301 --> 01:00:02.550
There was already
a winning machine there.

01:00:02.660 --> 01:00:06.653
Exactly. It was already built.
I can’t be that egotistical and say,

01:00:06.770 --> 01:00:08.926
"Barcelona is much better
because of me."

01:00:09.063 --> 01:00:12.356
But it wasn’t like that. -Yeah…
-It was already like that. -But Inter was.

01:00:12.516 --> 01:00:16.796
So, Mancini and then Mourinho comes…
-Mancini was there for two years.

01:00:16.933 --> 01:00:20.173
And then Mourinho arrived.
-And you clicked immediately, right?

01:00:20.319 --> 01:00:24.719
You and Mourinho? -It was…
Yes, immediately. I can say immediately.

01:00:24.887 --> 01:00:26.487
He’s special.

01:00:27.460 --> 01:00:29.180
He was…

01:00:29.580 --> 01:00:35.140
He wasn’t Capello, but he was
a modern version of Capello.

01:00:35.340 --> 01:00:40.700
Discipline like Capello’s,
that tactics, the way he spoke,

01:00:40.900 --> 01:00:45.900
the manipulation of players, how he talked
to the newspapers at press conferences…

01:00:46.340 --> 01:00:49.860
That was something new.
Every day, something was happening.

01:00:50.060 --> 01:00:54.340
On his first day in Italy he says:
"I’m not an idiot!"

01:00:54.540 --> 01:00:59.260
He says that at a press conference.
Everyone was saying: "What is this?"

01:00:59.740 --> 01:01:04.300
So, he was already prepared
for what was going to happen.

01:01:04.500 --> 01:01:06.580
He has his own way of finishing things

01:01:06.780 --> 01:01:11.700
and he knows how the game
should be played.

01:01:12.620 --> 01:01:19.740
He was a coach who manipulated
players and motivated them.

01:01:20.260 --> 01:01:25.660
He didn't come here to invent science.
He prepared the matches.

01:01:25.900 --> 01:01:29.940
You go into a match
and make two assists.

01:01:30.180 --> 01:01:34.110
All players say the same thing.
You were ready to kill for him,

01:01:34.517 --> 01:01:38.117
because that’s how he prepared
you and got into your head.

01:01:38.660 --> 01:01:42.300
When I was on the pitch,
no one could touch me.

01:01:42.580 --> 01:01:51.220
Now I’m flying, he came
and gave me a huge desire to win.

01:01:54.020 --> 01:01:58.700
At that moment he was at the top.
-After Chelsea?

01:01:59.020 --> 01:02:04.820
After Chelsea, he was The Special One.
Something was always happening.

01:02:05.580 --> 01:02:09.035
When you take those five…
You had that luck…

01:02:09.141 --> 01:02:11.181
which you deserved, of course.

01:02:11.381 --> 01:02:17.141
Capello, Mourinho, Guardiola, Ancelotti,
Mancini, and there were other great ones.

01:02:17.403 --> 01:02:19.043
They were different.

01:02:19.236 --> 01:02:21.636
I’m not asking who was better,
but what made them specific?

01:02:21.908 --> 01:02:25.388
They changed me to be better.

01:02:27.900 --> 01:02:31.260
Mourinho lifted me.

01:02:31.540 --> 01:02:35.420
The way he prepared matches,
no one did it like that.

01:02:35.580 --> 01:02:38.460
Capello changed my mentality.

01:02:41.340 --> 01:02:46.180
He understood what I needed to do
on the pitch to help the team.

01:02:46.980 --> 01:02:50.540
And because of that I respect him,
because that was important to me.

01:02:50.740 --> 01:02:57.380
Koeman gave me the chance to regain
confidence, to come back.

01:02:57.740 --> 01:02:59.900
Guardiola had a bit…

01:03:00.140 --> 01:03:07.100
Then something happened,
but for football, Guardiola was a maniac.

01:03:08.500 --> 01:03:13.474
He had a system.
Football 24 hours a day.

01:03:13.654 --> 01:03:15.724
All the time it was football,
football, football…

01:03:15.889 --> 01:03:20.670
He breathed, slept and ate football.
Do you understand?

01:03:22.100 --> 01:03:27.460
He had an answer for everything.
How to attack…

01:03:28.180 --> 01:03:30.500
A solution for everything.

01:03:30.700 --> 01:03:36.580
In Barcelona, how we played in
posession, from the back and all that...

01:03:37.340 --> 01:03:41.700
There were teams that tried to close
us down immediately. -To press.

01:03:41.900 --> 01:03:43.980
He says: "Ibra, no problem.

01:03:44.180 --> 01:03:48.460
Xavi goes as a false nine,
you drop behind, into midfield,

01:03:48.620 --> 01:03:50.700
and you play in that position.

01:03:50.900 --> 01:03:54.220
The ball comes from the goalkeeper there…
and we start playing."

01:03:54.420 --> 01:03:57.700
He had a solution for everything.
-For everything.

01:03:58.700 --> 01:04:04.060
So as a coach, in terms
of information, he was top.

01:04:04.260 --> 01:04:08.700
Despite the situation between us,
he was top. -That’s something else.

01:04:09.100 --> 01:04:14.117
I have to say he was top, the best coach.
And he changed football.

01:04:14.680 --> 01:04:18.133
Everything is a product of him.
-It’s his consequence.

01:04:18.324 --> 01:04:20.524
But not everyone is him,
that’s the problem.

01:04:20.709 --> 01:04:25.509
He said: "When we lose the ball, you
have three to five seconds to recover,

01:04:25.780 --> 01:04:28.900
and after five seconds, we come back."

01:04:29.100 --> 01:04:33.420
I’d never heard any coach
say something like that.

01:04:33.542 --> 01:04:38.862
Not Mourinho, not Capello, not Koeman,
no one… Not even Ancelotti.

01:04:39.069 --> 01:04:46.469
Ancelotti is a manager.
Old school, but he’s good. -Warm?

01:04:47.060 --> 01:04:51.020
Too warm, like a father,
a friend, everything.

01:04:51.900 --> 01:04:54.140
No one had a problem with him.

01:04:54.340 --> 01:04:57.780
If you didn’t play, you still
didn’t have a problem.

01:04:57.980 --> 01:05:00.420
They say he’s the best.
-Satisfied? -Yes.

01:05:00.620 --> 01:05:03.220
Everyone was satisfied because
there were no problems.

01:05:03.422 --> 01:05:06.702
He had that feeling of wanting
to be good with everyone.

01:05:07.086 --> 01:05:14.206
I ask him: "How do you do it?"
We had this situation… -Right wing.

01:05:14.500 --> 01:05:18.660
Two players played one match.
Then the next match, half and half.

01:05:18.900 --> 01:05:25.420
"How do you control that? They should
be grateful  and move forward."

01:05:25.780 --> 01:05:28.380
"It’s easy, Ibra."
-So what do you tell them?"

01:05:28.580 --> 01:05:32.500
"To one player I say
he’s the best in the team,

01:05:32.660 --> 01:05:36.460
then I go to the other and say
the same thing." -The same?

01:05:37.100 --> 01:05:40.060
That’s how he treated them.
I said: "OK."

01:05:40.260 --> 01:05:46.900
Then another situation... we’re out,
in a restaurant, it’s ten at night.

01:05:47.220 --> 01:05:54.180
We’re there, eating and drinking beer,
seven or eight of us players.

01:05:54.380 --> 01:05:57.940
Someone says: "Call Carlo
to come." Carlo Ancelotti...

01:05:58.180 --> 01:06:04.660
You call him and in 20 minutes
he’s with us, drinking… -Beer.

01:06:05.580 --> 01:06:08.780
After 45 minutes he says:
"You carry on, I’m going home."

01:06:08.980 --> 01:06:11.420
That’s how he was. -Huge.

01:06:11.940 --> 01:06:14.580
He was that good.

01:06:15.620 --> 01:06:20.860
At one training session I touch him like
this and call him: "Mister, mister…"

01:06:21.232 --> 01:06:25.312
He looks at me and says: "Who told
you, you can touch me like that?"

01:06:25.780 --> 01:06:33.015
I was shocked. I say: "Carlo?"
He says: "Relax." I’m joking.

01:06:33.220 --> 01:06:36.580
I tell him: "Carlo, don’t…" Scare me.

01:06:36.780 --> 01:06:40.620
He shock me, because that’s not him.
That’s how good he was. -Incredible.

01:06:40.820 --> 01:06:45.660
A good man. That’s why I think he
had success… -At Real Madrid, yes.

01:06:45.814 --> 01:06:48.471
For Real Madrid, you don’t need science.

01:06:48.600 --> 01:06:51.214
You need someone who knows
how to motivate everyone properly.

